   Title 17 Regulations,
   Lanterman Act & Related Laws


   The publication "A Consumer's Guide to the Lanterman Act" is now
   available. It is a 52-page booklet for adults with developmental
   disabilities and was written with the help of consumers.

   You can download the Adobe Acrobat PDF version of the guide using the
   following link. Please note that the file is 1,693KB in size and
   requires Version 5 of the free Adobe Acrobat Reader to be correctly
   viewed and printed.

                   A Consumer's Guide to the Lanterman Act

   If you would like a printed copy of the guide, please email your
   request to pclark@dds.ca.gov or send a written request to the following
   address:


    Department of Developmental Services
    Office of Human Rights & Advocacy Services
    Attn: CONSUMER'S GUIDE
    1600 Ninth Street, Room 240, MS 2-15
    Sacramento, CA 95814

   Include in the request your name, organization name, and how many
   copies you would like. As there is a limited supply of these booklets,
   requests numbering more than 5 copies per address will be filled on an
   as-needed basis.

   Note: Copies of the Consumer's Guide will be mailed directly to
   regional centers, area boards, developmental centers, family resource
   centers, and other constituents during the month of August.

   Adobe Acrobat Reader:
   If you do not have a copy of the Adobe Acrobat Reader, it is available
   for free online from Adobe.

